You can sort the map based on the index of occurrence of the *key* of the map in the given list by using a `Comparator` then to preserve the sort order collect it to a `LinkedHashMap` :

    public static void main(String[] args) throws Exception {
            Map&lt;String, Integer&gt; map = new HashMap&lt;&gt;();
            map.put(&quot;grocery&quot;, 150);
            map.put(&quot;utility&quot;, 130);
            map.put(&quot;miscellneous&quot;, 90);
            map.put(&quot;rent&quot;, 1150);
            map.put(&quot;clothes&quot;, 120);
            map.put(&quot;transportation&quot;, 100);
    
            List&lt;String&gt; list = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;(
                                Arrays.asList(&quot;utility&quot;, &quot;miscellneous&quot;, &quot;clothes&quot;, 
                                              &quot;transportation&quot;, &quot;rent&quot;));
            Map&lt;String, Integer&gt; sortedMap 
            = map.keySet()
                 .stream()
                 .filter(list::contains)
                 .sorted(Comparator.comparing(list::indexOf))
                 .collect(LinkedHashMap::new, 
                         (linkMap, key) -&gt; linkMap.put(key, map.get(key)), 
                         Map::putAll);
    
            System.out.println(sortedMap);
     }

